  "commentary": "With SPX at 6781 sitting right below the massive +12.7B gamma wall at 6800, dealers are positioned to aggressively sell any push higher into that strike, creating strong resistance. The PIN regime with 81B in total GEX suggests dealers will continue their stabilizing behavior - selling the current level and any rallies while buying dips back toward 6750-6785 support cluster. Watch 6800 as the critical rejection level and 6678 GEX flip as the line in the sand - a break below flips dealers short gamma and changes the game entirely.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get capped near 6800 and grind sideways between 6750-6800.",
